      <h2>Latest Department news</h2> 
      <p> 
       <!--
<img src="assets/images/doon_240x180.jpg" alt="The Doon, Arran" height="180" width="240" />
<h4>Arran fieldtrip</h4>
<p>
After a wet and wind-swept time up on Arran, the first year geologists returned with lots of stories to tell.
</p>
<p>
This photo shows The Doon, on the coast of Arran, a large composite sill that displays columnar jointing.&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
The Arran fieldtrip is designed to introduce first-years to a wide range of geological formations and features, and to introduce them to the mapping and observation skills they will need as geologists.&nbsp;
</p>
--> </p>
      <div class="homepage_news_item"> 
       <h4><a href="news/research-news/death-of-a-dynamo-a-hard-drive-from-space" title="Death of a dynamo – a hard drive from space">Death of a dynamo – a hard drive from space</a></h4> 
       <h1>
        <!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
</xml><![endif]-->Death of a dynamo - a hard drive from space</h1> 
       <h1> </h1> 
       <p class="MsoNormal"> The dying moments of an asteroid’s magnetic field have been successfully captured by a research team led by <a href="people/academic-staff/richard-harrison">Richard Harrison</a>, in a study that offers a tantalising glimpse of what may happen to the Earth’s magnetic core billions of years from now. </p> 
       <p class="MsoNormal"> <a href="http://www.cam.ac.uk/research/news/death-of-a-dynamo-a-hard-drive-from-space">Read more</a> </p> 
       <p> &nbsp; </p> 
       <p> &nbsp; </p> 
       <p> &nbsp; </p> 
       <!--![endif]---->
       <!--!--[if--> 
       <a href="news/research-news/death-of-a-dynamo-a-hard-drive-from-space" title="Read more...">Read more...</a> 
